House Resolution 123
By: Representatives Buckner of the 137th and Burnough of the 77th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 4, 2025, as Girl Scout Day at the state capitol and commending Girl
2 Scouts as a national leader in providing the best leadership development experience in the
3 world to American girls; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, more than a century ago, native Savannahian Juliette Gordon Low started the
5 movement known as Girl Scouts. Beginning with the first gathering of 18 girls in Savannah
6 on March 12, 1912, Juliette broke the conventions of the time by reaching across class,
7 cultural, and ethnic boundaries to ensure that all girls, including those with disabilities, had
8 a place to grow and develop their talents and leadership skills; and
9 WHEREAS, the life mission of Juliette Gordon Low was to build girls of courage,
10 confidence, and character; and
11 WHEREAS, the Girl Scout Leadership Experience encourages girls to develop a strong sense
12 of self, connect to their communities both locally and globally, and feel empowered to make
13 a difference in the world; and
